                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d165">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/52<hi rend="superscript">3/16</hi>:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cousins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-15T11:00:00-06:00"
                            >July 15, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>44. Referring to the Department’s strictly confidential circular telegram of July
                    11, 4 p.m.,<note n="82" xml:id="d165fn1">See footnote 29, <ref target="#pg_16"
                            >p. 16</ref>.</note> I informed President Carías of the contents thereof
                    and he will be very pleased to have the proposed <pb facs="0143" n="131"
                        xml:id="pg_131"/> staff conversations take place at the pleasure of the
                    United States Government. His attitude is one of complete cooperation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cousins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
